WEBVTT

00:02:59.014 --> 00:03:00.786
"North-northeast in the far distance.

00:03:00.810 --> 00:03:02.131
How about you?"

00:03:02.155 --> 00:03:05.287
So imagine as you're walking
around your day,

00:03:05.311 --> 00:03:06.860
every person you greet,

00:03:06.884 --> 00:03:08.955
you have to report your heading direction.

00:03:08.979 --> 00:03:10.158
(Laughter)

00:03:10.182 --> 00:03:13.513
But that would actually get you
oriented pretty fast, right?

00:03:13.537 --> 00:03:16.497
Because you literally
couldn't get past "hello,"

00:03:16.521 --> 00:03:18.596
if you didn't know
which way you were going.

00:03:19.969 --> 00:03:23.461
In fact, people who speak languages
like this stay oriented really well.

00:03:23.485 --> 00:03:26.410
They stay oriented better
than we used to think humans could.

